                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-309-off1672 t18250915-309-victim1560"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>JOHN GIBBS. I am in the <rs id="t18250915-309-viclabel1674" type="occupation">employ of the Excise</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-309-victim1560 t18250915-309-viclabel1674"></join>, and live in Kinder-street, St. Georges's, in the East. On the 11th of July, between four and five o'clock in the afternoon, I was going from the Excise-office, Tower-street, home - I stood in <placeName id="t18250915-309-crimeloc1675">Rosemary-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-309-crimeloc1675" type="placeName" value="Rosemary-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-309-crimeloc1675" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-309-off1672 t18250915-309-crimeloc1675"></join>, about two minutes, to look at something, and felt a hand at my right hand coat pocket: I put my hand down and missed my handkerchief - I turned round and said to the prisoner, "You have picked my pocket;" he was the nearest person to me, and was close to me - he said, "I have not;" I laid hold of him, and in pulling his coat open, found the handkerchief concealed under his left arm; I took him to the watch-house - it happened on the north side of the way, eight or ten doors from the Minories.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-309-person1561">
                  JOSEPH 
                  STONE
               <interp inst="t18250915-309-person1561" type="surname" value="STONE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-309-person1561" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-309-person1561" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable, and the prisoner was delivered to me; he allowed that the handkerchief was in his possession; he said, it was given to him by another person - the spot the prosecutor has described, is in the City; it extends fourteen or fifteen houses down.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-309-person1562">
                  JOHN 
                  LACY HAWKINS
               <interp inst="t18250915-309-person1562" type="surname" value="LACY HAWKINS"></interp>
